---
layout: page.njk
title: Amherst Community Band
description: The homepage of the Amherst Community Band from Amherst, Massachusetts.
---
<section>
    <div class="hero-body pt-2">
        <div class="carousel"
        data-flickity='{"setGallerySize":true}'>
            {% for slide in config.carouselImages %}
                <div class="carousel-cell">
                    <p class="is-size-3 has-text-centered">{{ slide.caption|safe }}</p>
                    {% image "src" + slide.imgPath, slide.altText, "(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw" %}
                </div>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


<section class="section has-background-info-light">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="columns is-centered">
            <div class="column is-two-thirds">
                <h2 class="title has-text-centered">Rehearsals begin Monday, June 8, 2026!</h2>
                <p>Our Summer season is right around the corner. We're planning an exciting lineup of music and guest conductors. If you play an instrument, please consider joining us. All are welcome!</p>
                <br>
                <div class="has-text-centered">
                    <a class="button" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1nuJW-ZWfX4PpOa5TBXrIaNZX7z1w-D5yCEj5n_BbWLw/edit#response=ACYDBNi9KF_sG6WK7TuISavmooIY58MvRhoPU1S-JDF0rV94UQX7Nj6rtuBnhbGfvvjCRj4">Amherst Community Band 2026 Season Signup Form</a>
                    <br><br>
                    <a class="has-text-weight-medium" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1BAiRqI2M5HVDRtvIcswyIRhhGg_DB7npbs3DAl_eka8/edit?usp=sharing">Here's the schedule for the full season.</a>
                </div>
                <br>
                <p class="has-text-centered has-text-weight-bold">We are grateful to our scheduled guest conductors!</p>
                <br>
                <div class="columns is-centered">
                    <div class="column is-narrow has-text-centered">
                        <p><strong>June 27 &amp; July 3 Concerts</strong><br>
                        Dave Morris, Conductor<br>
                        Alexandria (Lexie) Black, Assistant Conductor</p>
                        <br>

                        <p><strong>July 25 Concert</strong><br>
                        Juli Sansoucy, Conductor</p>
                        <br>

                        <p><strong>August 15 &amp; 18 Concerts</strong><br>
                        Richard Cuoco, Conductor</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="columns">
        <div class="column is-flex">
            <div class="container has-background-primary-light has-text-centered p-5 has-soft-corners">
                <p>The Amherst Community Band is made up of high school students, college students, and adults, some of whom are in their 80's!  Whether you play right now, or you haven’t played in years, you’ll feel right at home. Best of all we're audition free!</p>
                <br>
                <div class="container has-text-centered">
                    <a class="button" href="/join/">Join Us!</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-flex">
            <div class="container has-background-grey-lighter has-text-centered p-5 has-soft-corners">
                <p>Our band is always under construction.  Help us buy music, rent trucks and make music in our community with your generous online contributions!</p>
                <br>
                <div class="container has-text-centered">
                    <a class="button" href="https://www.zeffy.com/donation-form/keep-the-music-playing">Donate on Zeffy!</a>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-flex">
            <div class="container has-background-success has-text-centered p-5 has-soft-corners">
                <p>We play concerts in Amherst, MA all summer long and have a holiday concert in December! All concerts are free and open to the public. After all, without an audience, it's only a rehearsal!</p>
                <br>
                <div class="container has-text-centered">
                    <a class="button" href="/performances/">See us play!</a>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section pt-1">
    <div class="columns is-centered is-8">
        <div class="column is-3">
            <a href="http://www.massculturalcouncil.org/">
                {% image "src/_images/MCC_Logo_RGB_NoTag.png", "Mass Cultural Council Logo", "(max-height: auto)" %}
            </a>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-3">
            {% image "src/_images/amherst_cultural_council.jpg", "Amherst Cultural Council Logo", "(max-height: auto)" %}
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container has-text-centered">
        <h2 class="title is-4">This program is funded in part by a grant from the Amherst Cultural Council, a local agency which is supported by Mass Cultural Council, a state agency.</h2>
    </div>
</section>
